{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QY7vjzqPdWY6nJ7wqcYis1","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→\"\"\"\n     2→Single task execution script — for inner loop success criteria evaluation.\n     3→python run_task.py\n     4→\n     5→Success criteria: output contains \"CORRECT\"\n     6→\"\"\"\n     7→\n     8→import sys\n     9→import traceback\n    10→\n    11→TASK_HEX = \"08ed6ac7\"\n    12→MAX_STEPS = 500  # Allow enough iterations until goal is achieved\n    13→\n    14→\n    15→def main():\n    16→    print(f\"=== run_task: {TASK_HEX} ===\\n\")\n    17→\n    18→    # 1. Load task\n    19→    print(\"[*] Loading task...\")\n    20→    try:\n    21→        from basics.viz import show_task\n    22→        from managers.arc_manager import ARCManager\n    23→\n    24→        manager = ARCManager(data_root=\"data\", semantic_memory_root=\"semantic_memory\")\n    25→        task = manager.load_task(TASK_HEX)\n    26→        print(f\"    Task: {task}\")\n    27→        show_task(task)\n    28→\n    29→    except Exception:\n    30→        print(\"[!] Task loading failed:\")\n    31→        traceback.print_exc()\n    32→        sys.exit(1)\n    33→\n    34→    print(\"\\n[*] WM + SOAR cycle (Elaborate → Propose → Select → Apply)...\")\n    35→    try:\n    36→        from agent.wm import WorkingMemory\n    37→        from agent.wm_logger import print_wm_triplets, reset_wm_snapshot\n    38→        from agent.io import inject_arc_task\n    39→        from agent.elaboration_rules import build_elaborator\n    40→        from agent.rules import build_proposer\n    41→        from agent.cycle import run_cycle\n    42→\n    43→        wm = WorkingMemory()\n    44→\n    45→        reset_wm_snapshot(wm)\n    46→        print_wm_triplets(wm, label=\"Initial WM (before input)\", step=0)\n    47→\n    48→        inject_arc_task(task, wm)\n    49→        print_wm_triplets(wm, label=\"After input-link injection (before cycle)\", step=0)\n    50→\n    51→        elaborator = build_elaborator()\n    52→        proposer = build_proposer()\n    53→\n    54→        out = run_cycle(\n    55→            wm,\n    56→            elaborator,\n    57→            proposer,\n    58→            max_steps=MAX_STEPS,\n    59→            stop_on_goal=True,\n    60→            log_wm=True,\n    61→        )\n    62→        print(f\"\\n[cycle] {out}\")\n    63→\n    64→    except Exception:\n    65→        print(\"[!] WM / cycle failed:\")\n    66→        traceback.print_exc()\n    67→        _print_result(False, error=True)\n    68→        sys.exit(1)\n    69→\n    70→    # 2. Result evaluation\n    71→    # Extract submitted answer from wm\n    72→    try:\n    73→        predicted = _extract_prediction(wm)\n    74→        answer = _load_answer(task)\n    75→        correct = _check_correct(predicted, answer)\n    76→        _print_result(correct)\n    77→        sys.exit(0 if correct else 1)\n    78→\n    79→    except Exception:\n    80→        print(\"[!] Result evaluation failed:\")\n    81→        traceback.print_exc()\n    82→        _print_result(False, error=True)\n    83→        sys.exit(1)\n    84→\n    85→\n    86→def _extract_prediction(wm):\n    87→    \"\"\"\n    88→    Extract the predicted grid from the WM output-link.\n    89→    SubmitOperator must write the result to the following slots:\n    90→      (S1 ^output-link O_out)\n    91→      (O_out ^predicted-grid [[...], [...], ...])\n    92→    Returns None until implemented.\n    93→    \"\"\"\n    94→    try:\n    95→        s1 = wm.get(\"S1\")\n    96→        output_link_id = s1.get(\"output-link\")\n    97→        if not output_link_id:\n    98→            return None\n    99→        output_node = wm.get(output_link_id)\n   100→        if not output_node:\n   101→            return None\n   102→        return output_node.get(\"predicted-grid\")\n   103→    except Exception:\n   104→        return None\n   105→\n   106→\n   107→def _load_answer(task):\n   108→    \"\"\"\n   109→    Extract the correct output grid from the task object's test pairs.\n   110→    Returns a list if there are multiple test pairs.\n   111→    \"\"\"\n   112→    answers = []\n   113→    for pair in task.test_pairs:\n   114→        if hasattr(pair, \"output\") and pair.output is not None:\n   115→            answers.append(pair.output.contents)\n   116→    return answers if answers else None\n   117→\n   118→\n   119→def _check_correct(predicted, answer):\n   120→    \"\"\"\n   121→    predicted: predicted grid (list[list[int]] or list of them)\n   122→    answer:    list of correct grids\n   123→    Returns True only on exact match.\n   124→    \"\"\"\n   125→    if predicted is None or answer is None:\n   126→        return False\n   127→    # Wrap in a list if a single grid was provided\n   128→    if predicted and not isinstance(predicted[0], list):\n   129→        predicted = [predicted]\n   130→    if len(predicted) != len(answer):\n   131→        return False\n   132→    for pred, ans in zip(predicted, answer):\n   133→        if pred != ans:\n   134→            return False\n   135→    return True\n   136→\n   137→\n   138→def _print_result(correct: bool, error: bool = False):\n   139→    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 40)\n   140→    if error:\n   141→        print(\"RESULT  : ERROR (unable to evaluate)\")\n   142→    elif correct:\n   143→        print(\"RESULT  : CORRECT ✅\")\n   144→    else:\n   145→        print(\"RESULT  : INCORRECT ❌\")\n   146→    print(\"=\" * 40)\n   147→\n   148→\n   149→if __name__ == \"__main__\":\n   150→    main()"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"ee60c734-c338-4862-b4f6-26a79e7358e9","timestamp":"2026-03-24T09:33:03.821Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\Sir_K\\Desktop\\SOAR-ARC-test\\run_task.py","content":"\"\"\"\nSingle task execution script — for inner loop success criteria evaluation.\npython run_task.py\n\nSuccess criteria: output contains \"CORRECT\"\n\"\"\"\n\nimport sys\nimport traceback\n\nTASK_HEX = \"08ed6ac7\"\nMAX_STEPS = 500  # Allow enough iterations until goal is achieved\n\n\ndef main():\n    print(f\"=== run_task: {TASK_HEX} ===\\n\")\n\n    # 1. Load task\n    print(\"[*] Loading task...\")\n    try:\n        from basics.viz import show_task\n        from managers.arc_manager import ARCManager\n\n        manager = ARCManager(data_root=\"data\", semantic_memory_root=\"semantic_memory\")\n        task = manager.load_task(TASK_HEX)\n        print(f\"    Task: {task}\")\n        show_task(task)\n\n    except Exception:\n        print(\"[!] Task loading failed:\")\n        traceback.print_exc()\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    print(\"\\n[*] WM + SOAR cycle (Elaborate → Propose → Select → Apply)...\")\n    try:\n        from agent.wm import WorkingMemory\n        from agent.wm_logger import print_wm_triplets, reset_wm_snapshot\n        from agent.io import inject_arc_task\n        from agent.elaboration_rules import build_elaborator\n        from agent.rules import build_proposer\n        from agent.cycle import run_cycle\n\n        wm = WorkingMemory()\n\n        reset_wm_snapshot(wm)\n        print_wm_triplets(wm, label=\"Initial WM (before input)\", step=0)\n\n        inject_arc_task(task, wm)\n        print_wm_triplets(wm, label=\"After input-link injection (before cycle)\", step=0)\n\n        elaborator = build_elaborator()\n        proposer = build_proposer()\n\n        out = run_cycle(\n            wm,\n            elaborator,\n            proposer,\n            max_steps=MAX_STEPS,\n            stop_on_goal=True,\n            log_wm=True,\n        )\n        print(f\"\\n[cycle] {out}\")\n\n    except Exception:\n        print(\"[!] WM / cycle failed:\")\n        traceback.print_exc()\n        _print_result(False, error=True)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    # 2. Result evaluation\n    # Extract submitted answer from wm\n    try:\n        predicted = _extract_prediction(wm)\n        answer = _load_answer(task)\n        correct = _check_correct(predicted, answer)\n        _print_result(correct)\n        sys.exit(0 if correct else 1)\n\n    except Exception:\n        print(\"[!] Result evaluation failed:\")\n        traceback.print_exc()\n        _print_result(False, error=True)\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n\ndef _extract_prediction(wm):\n    \"\"\"\n    Extract the predicted grid from the WM output-link.\n    SubmitOperator must write the result to the following slots:\n      (S1 ^output-link O_out)\n      (O_out ^predicted-grid [[...], [...], ...])\n    Returns None until implemented.\n    \"\"\"\n    try:\n        s1 = wm.get(\"S1\")\n        output_link_id = s1.get(\"output-link\")\n        if not output_link_id:\n            return None\n        output_node = wm.get(output_link_id)\n        if not output_node:\n            return None\n        return output_node.get(\"predicted-grid\")\n    except Exception:\n        return None\n\n\ndef _load_answer(task):\n    \"\"\"\n    Extract the correct output grid from the task object's test pairs.\n    Returns a list if there are multiple test pairs.\n    \"\"\"\n    answers = []\n    for pair in task.test_pairs:\n        if hasattr(pair, \"output\") and pair.output is not None:\n            answers.append(pair.output.contents)\n    return answers if answers else None\n\n\ndef _check_correct(predicted, answer):\n    \"\"\"\n    predicted: predicted grid (list[list[int]] or list of them)\n    answer:    list of correct grids\n    Returns True only on exact match.\n    \"\"\"\n    if predicted is None or answer is None:\n        return False\n    # Wrap in a list if a single grid was provided\n    if predicted and not isinstance(predicted[0], list):\n        predicted = [predicted]\n    if len(predicted) != len(answer):\n        return False\n    for pred, ans in zip(predicted, answer):\n        if pred != ans:\n            return False\n    return True\n\n\ndef _print_result(correct: bool, error: bool = False):\n    print(\"\\n\" + \"=\" * 40)\n    if error:\n        print(\"RESULT  : ERROR (unable to evaluate)\")\n    elif correct:\n        print(\"RESULT  : CORRECT ✅\")\n    else:\n        print(\"RESULT  : INCORRECT ❌\")\n    print(\"=\" * 40)\n\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()","numLines":150,"startLine":1,"totalLines":150}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_01Y2g2ZgR5nbjFQKQqDE4xUr","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the situation. The error is a `UnicodeEncodeError` in `wm_logger.py` because of box-drawing characters that can't be encoded with cp949. Let me read the key files I still need:\n\n1. `agent/wm_logger.py` - to fix the Unicode error\n2. `agent/wm.py` - to understand WM structure\n3. `agent/io.py` - to understand task injection\n4. `agent/elaboration_rules.py` - to understand elaboration\n5. `ARCKG/comparison.py` - to understand compare()\n\n\n6. The task data itself to see what we're working with\n\nThe Unicode error in wm_logger.py is blocking me, so I'll tackle that first before moving on to the operator implementations. Looking at the priority list from PROMPT.md, I need to implement DeepenOperator, the top-scope-no-detail rule, and several comparison and analysis operators in sequence.\n\nBut first, I need to get past this Unicode issue so the task can actually run. Let me explore more of the codebase to understand the system architecture.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":12150,"cache_read_input_tokens":28085,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":12150},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"257de878-fc9d-48ea-9f06-060eecd20b6c","uuid":"40169b3b-a2e0-478b-bbbd-ad275cc63ed2"}
